---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const locale = 'en' as const;
---

<Base locale={locale} title="About — Azizbek Umidjonov">
  <article class="max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">About</h1>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-fg)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer based in Seoul. I build consumer products
        and the infrastructure that runs them — Android, web, backends,
        and increasingly the CI/CD and observability that holds it all
        together.
      </p>

      <p>
        I've shipped a profitable English-learning app solo (100K+
        downloads), contributed to Hono.js, published an OSS payment
        library used in production, and am currently the tech co-founder
        of a live-commerce translation startup pushing real-time
        multilingual video through AWS Fargate.
      </p>

      <p>
        My engineering values are pragmatic. I favor clean architecture
        because it keeps debugging cheap, testing at three tiers because
        bugs hide between layers, and observability because production is
        the only place that matters. I don't over-engineer — ship, measure,
        iterate.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">What I'm looking for</h2>
      <p>
        Senior-level engineering roles in Korea — ideally Android, platform,
        or full-stack positions where the team ships consumer-facing products
        and cares about craft.
      </p>
      <p>
        I hold an E-7 visa, so I'm work-authorized in Korea today. I'm
        studying Korean actively (beginner level).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">Background</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-[var(--color-fg)]">
        <li>Coding since 2019, full-time professional since 2020</li>
        <li>Previous: StoneLab (Android + mobile + frontend, Seoul)</li>
        <li>Before that: CodemyUz (2020, Uzbekistan)</li>
        <li>Side projects: Spiko English (solo), Brivva Tech (co-founded)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">Beyond code</h2>
      <p>
        I use NixOS + Obsidian + terminal-heavy workflows. I read more than
        I write. I'm slowly building a Korean vocabulary that will, one
        day, let me stop apologizing in English at the convenience store.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a
        href="/resume-android.pdf"
        class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-sm hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
      >
        Résumé — Android
      </a>
      <a
        href="/resume-backend.pdf"
        class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-sm hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
      >
        Résumé — Backend
      </a>
      <a
        href="/resume-frontend.pdf"
        class="border border-[var(--color-border)] px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-sm hover:border-[var(--color-accent)]"
      >
        Résumé — Frontend
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
